# Pi Runtime Deploy Safety

When changes affect Pi behavior, do not mark work complete until runtime parity is verified.

- Treat these as separate states: dev repo, Pi repo, Pi runtime (`/opt/ui`, `/opt/wsbridge`).
- Never assume service names or paths; verify on device from `systemctl cat` and active units.
- After every Pi-facing change, provide exact deploy commands for touched files only.
- Require restart of only relevant services and report the exact units restarted.
- Require post-deploy verification commands:
  - Source vs runtime hash checks for each touched file.
  - `systemctl is-active` for required services.
  - Targeted runtime grep/probe proving the intended change exists in runtime files.
- If verification is missing or fails, explicitly state "not deployed/verified yet".
- Prefer smallest safe change scope (one function/feature at a time) and verify before next change.
